        <li>Government data may be incomplete or change after we publish</li>
        <li>Articles are written with AI assistance and human review, but errors can occur</li>
        <li>Always verify critical information with the official source linked in each article</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>No Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE_NAME} is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or implied.
        We make no guarantees about the accuracy, completeness, reliability, or timeliness of
        our content.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, {SITE_NAME}, its operators, and contributors
        are not liable for any damages arising from your use of the site or reliance on its content.
      </p>
      <p>
        This includes but is not limited to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages</li>
        <li>Loss of data, revenue, or profits</li>
        <li>Personal injury or property damage</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>External Links</h2>
      <p>
        Articles on {SITE_NAME} link to official government websites. We are not responsible
        for the content, accuracy, or privacy practices of external sites.
      </p>

      <h2>User Conduct</h2>
      <p>
        You agree not to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the site for unlawful purposes</li>
        <li>Attempt to interfere with site operations or security</li>
        <li>Scrape or copy large portions of content without permission</li>
        <li>Misrepresent our content as official government communications</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        Government data published on {SITE_NAME} is in the public domain. Our original writing,
        design, and presentation are protected by copyright. You may link to our articles, but
        please don't copy them in full without attribution.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms of Use at any time. Changes take effect when posted.
        Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance.
      </p>

      <h2>Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of the United States. Any disputes will be
        resolved in the appropriate courts.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms? Email us at <a href="mailto:legal@areazine.com">legal@areazine.com</a>.
      </p>
